value.text:
(Personal Taste Food, year 1994, age 5) Traditional mother-made dishes,
pancake, (also nettle pancake)
Natural yogurt, honey and muesli
Ice cream,
Granny's layer cakes,
Granny's baked goods

In my early years, I was fortunate to have a traditional mother who made delicious dishes such as pancakes and nettle pancakes. Breakfast was often a tasty combination of natural yogurt, honey, and muesli, while dessert consisted of ice cream and Granny's famous layer cakes and baked goods. As I grew older, my palate expanded to include common meals made by my mother, and I developed a love for the pea soup served at school. My love for pancakes and nettle pancakes continued, as well as my love for yogurt and muesli for breakfast. Grandmother's layer cakes and pastries remained a sweet indulgence, along with occasional store-bought treats like candies, chips, chocolate, and soda. I also enjoyed cereals like Weetabix and corn flakes with milk, and indulged in chocolate milk as a special treat.

Growing up, my palate was shaped by my traditional mother's delicious dishes like pancakes and nettle pancakes. Breakfast was always a tasty mix of natural yogurt, honey, and muesli, while dessert was usually ice cream or treats from Granny's famous layer cakes and baked goods. As I got older, I developed a love for common meals and the pea soup served at school. My breakfast favorites remained the same, and I also indulged in store-bought snacks like candies, chips, and soda. Cereals like Weetabix and corn flakes were also a staple. Overall, my childhood was filled with a mix of homemade delights and occasional indulgences.

(Personal Taste Food, from year 1993 to year 1996, age 4 - 7) Growing up, my palate was shaped by my traditional mother's delicious dishes like pancakes and nettle pancakes. Breakfast was always a tasty mix of natural yogurt, honey, and muesli, while dessert was usually ice cream or treats from Granny's famous layer cakes and baked goods. As I got older, I developed a love for common meals and the pea soup served at school. My breakfast favorites remained the same, and I also indulged in store-bought snacks like candies, chips, and soda. Cereals like Weetabix and corn flakes were also a staple. Overall, my childhood was filled with a mix of homemade delights and occasional indulgences.

In the late 90s at the age of 8 and 9, I had a love for nostalgic foods like regular homemade meals cooked by my mom and school lunches, especially pea soup, pancakes (both regular and nettle), and yogurt with muesli. I also had a sweet tooth for ice cream, my grandma's cream cakes and pastries, and store-bought treats like candy, chips, chocolate, and soft drinks. Breakfast favorites included Weetabix, chocolate milk, and corn flakes with milk. And who could resist mouthwatering oven-baked pizzas and warm cheese sandwiches straight from the oven?

Year 1999-2000, Age 10-11:
Home-cooked meals by mom,
School lunches like pea soup and pancakes,
Yogurt and muesli,
Ice cream and store-bought treats,
Grandma's cream cakes and pastries,
Weetabix and chocolate milk,
Oven-baked pizza and warm cheese sandwiches,
Traditional dishes,
Apple and orange juice,
Bread with cheese and cold cuts.

During my early years in the late 90s, at the age of 8-11, my taste in food revolved around traditional home-cooked meals made by my mom such as pea soup, pancakes, and yogurt with muesli. I also had a love for sweet treats like ice cream, my grandma's baked goods, and store-bought indulgences like candy and chips. Breakfast favorites included Weetabix, chocolate milk, and corn flakes with milk, and nothing beat mouthwatering oven-baked pizzas and cheese sandwiches. As I grew older, I also developed a taste for traditional dishes, as well as bread with cheese and cold cuts. And for drinks, apple and orange juice always hit the spot.

Personal Taste Food, 2001-2002, Ages 12-13:
Traditional mother-made dishes,
School meals (pancakes, oven-baked pizza),
Warm cheese toasties,
Yogurt and muesli,
Ice cream,
Grandma's cakes and pastries,
Store-bought treats (candies, chips, chocolate, soda),
Corn flakes and milk,
Apple juice,
Orange juice,
Bread with cheese and cold cuts.

Common food choices at age 14-15: Home-cooked meals, school lunches (pancakes, oven pizza, sandwiches), yogurt and muesli, ice cream, grandma's baked goods, store-bought treats (candies, chips, chocolate, soda), fruit juices, bread with cheese and cold cuts.

Personal Taste Food, 2001-2004, Ages 12-15:
Traditional mother-made dishes, school meals, warm cheese toasties, yogurt and muesli, ice cream, grandma's baked goods, store-bought treats, cereal and milk, fruit juices, bread with cheese and cold cuts.

From 1997 to 2000, ages 8-11, my taste in food centered around delicious traditional dishes cooked by my mom such as pea soup, pancakes, and yogurt with muesli. I also had a sweet tooth for treats like ice cream, baked goods from my grandma, and store-bought indulgences like candy and chips. Breakfast favorites included Weetabix, chocolate milk, and corn flakes with milk, while oven-baked pizzas and cheese sandwiches were always a crowd-pleaser. As I grew older, I also developed a taste for traditional dishes, as well as bread with cheese and cold cuts. And for drinks, apple and orange juice always hit the spot. These culinary preferences continued into my teenage years from 2001 to 2004, ages 12-15, alongside school meals, warm cheese toasties, and fruit juices.

Growing up from 1989 to 2004, my taste in food was heavily influenced by my traditional mother's delicious dishes like pancakes, pea soup, and homemade baked goods. Breakfast consisted of natural yogurt, honey, muesli, and occasionally sugary snacks like candies and chips. As I got older, my love for traditional dishes grew along with a taste for convenience foods like pizza and cheese sandwiches. Fruit juices were my go-to drink, but I also enjoyed the occasional soda. Overall, my childhood and teenage years were a mix of wholesome homemade meals and indulgent treats.

My personal taste in food during the ages of 16 and 17 in 2005 and 2006 was a mix of traditional home-cooked meals from my mother, school lunches, and favorite treats like pancakes, oven-baked pizza, hot cheese sandwiches, yogurt and muesli, ice cream, and my grandmother's delicious cream cakes and pastries. I also enjoyed indulging in store-bought treats such as candy, chips, chocolate, and soda. I often accompanied my meals with apple or orange juice and snacked on bread with cheese and cold cuts. And of course, being a typical teenager, I also developed a taste for beer and wine during this time. Overall, my appetite was a balance of home-cooked meals and indulgent treats.

Traditional mother's home-cooked meals,

Pancakes,

Yogurt and muesli,
Ice cream,
Grandmother's cream cakes,

Personal Taste Food, from year 2005 to year 2008, age 16 - 19:
During my teenage years from 2005 to 2008, my taste in food was a mix of traditional home-cooked meals from my mother, school lunches, and indulgent treats like pancakes, pizza, and ice cream. I also enjoyed my grandmother's delicious cream cakes and pastries, along with store-bought treats and beverages like candy, chips, and beer. Overall, my appetite was a balance of home-cooked meals and tasty indulgences.

Starting from the year 2009, at the age of 20, my taste in food was heavily influenced by my usual home-cooked meals such as rice, potatoes, pasta, and various types of meat. During my time in school and the army, all of my meals were provided for, including pancakes, oven-baked pizza, and warm grilled cheese sandwiches. I also enjoyed treats like ice cream, grandma's layer cakes and pastries, as well as store-bought snacks like candy, chips, and soda. I would often sip on apple juice or orange juice, and occasionally indulge in bread with cheese and cold cuts, as well as beer and wine. As I got older and turned 21 in the year 2010, my taste in food remained similar with typical home-cooked meals still being a staple in my diet. I continued to enjoy pancakes, oven pizza, and grilled cheese sandwiches, as well as yogurt and muesli and my grandmother's creamy cakes and baked goods. Little changed in terms of my preference for store-bought treats and drinks like candy, chips, chocolate, soda, apple juice, orange juice, and bread with cheese and deli meat, along with beer and wine.

At home, we usually have classic home-cooked meals like rice, potatoes, pasta, chicken, and ground beef. When I was 22, I also enjoyed different dishes at school, including pancakes, pizza, and warm cheese sandwiches. Treats like yogurt, granola, ice cream, and pastries from my grandma's recipes were a favorite, along with store-bought items like candy, chips, chocolate, and soda. And of course, we always had apple juice, orange juice, bread with cheese and cold cuts, beer, and wine on hand. The following year, at age 23, my food preferences remained the same.

As I got older, my preference for meals and snacks remained similar, with staples like pancakes, pizza, and grilled cheese sandwiches, and drinks like apple juice, orange juice, and beer. Even at 22 and 23 years old, my food taste stayed mostly unchanged.

Even as I got older, my preference for meals and snacks remained similar, with staples like rice, potatoes, and grilled cheese sandwiches, along with drinks like apple juice, orange juice, and beer.

Kouluaikaan liikuin vapaa-ajalla erittäin vähän.
Koulussa oli liikuntatunteja.

Armeijassa oli alokasaikana keskitason fyysistä harjoittelua.

Sotilaspoliisialiupseeri-koulussa fyysinen harjoittelu voimistui huomattavasti.
Kävimme juoksemassa aamulenkin heti herätessämme.
Päivän harjoitukset olivat rankkoja ja varustuksemme oli painavampi kuin tavallisella miehistöllä luotiliivien takia.
years.text:
I rode my bike to school 1km - 2.3km.
During school time, I exercised very little in my free time.
There were physical education classes in school.

During basic training in the military, there was moderate level physical training.

At Military Police Officer School, the physical training intensified significantly.
We went for a morning run right after waking up.
The training exercises during the day were tough and we had heavier equipment due to the bulletproof vests.

years.keywords: Group leader, Military Police, Lapland Wing, Practice, Long exercises, Barracks, Training, Full gear, Exceptional reason, Home, Gym
years.native_text:
Sotilaspoliisi ryhmänjohtajana Lapin Lennostossa harjoittelimme todella paljon.
Harjoittelimme eniten kaikista sotilaspoliisi kompanjoista.
Meillä oli paljon pitkiä leirejä ja kasarmilla ollessa treenasimme ulkona täysvarustuksessa, ellei ollut poikkeuksellinen syy.

Kotona aloin käymään kuntosalilla.
years.text:
As a group leader in the Military Police in Lapland Wing, we practiced a lot.
We practiced more than any other Military Police company.
We had a lot of long exercises and when we were at the barracks, we trained outside in full gear, unless there was an exceptional reason.

At home, I started going to the gym.

At the age of 6, in 1995, I would occasionally go skiing in the winter and relish the few moments spent at the swimming hall. The following year, at the age of 7, I would cycle or walk 2km to and from school every weekday, and attend physical education classes. Skiing remained a favorite winter activity, with a few memorable trips, and I also cherished my visits to the swimming pool. These activities not only kept me active, but also brought me joy and taught me the value of staying physically fit.

The following year, at the age of 7, I would cycle or walk 2km to and from school every weekday, and attend physical education classes. Skiing remained a favorite winter activity, with a few memorable trips, and I also cherished my visits to the swimming pool. These activities not only kept me active, but also brought me joy and taught me the value of staying physically fit.

During my childhood, I had a strong appreciation for physical exercise. At the age of 8 and living in 1997, I would often cycle or walk the 2km route to and from school every weekday. I also had physical education classes at school and occasionally went skiing during the winter. Although I didn't get to go often, I thoroughly enjoyed my few trips to the swimming pool. The following year, when I was 9 and in 1998, I continued with my daily cycling routine and physical education classes. I also had opportunities to go skiing during the winter and loved my occasional visits to the swimming pool. My passion for staying active and physically fit continued to grow throughout my childhood.

At the age of 10 and 11, I incorporated physical exercise into my daily routine by biking or walking 2km or 1.7km to school. I also had physical education classes at school and went skiing occasionally during the winter months. Additionally, I went to the swimming pool once a week for extended periods.

As a child from 1997-2000, I had a strong appreciation for physical exercise. At the ages of 8 and 9, I cycled or walked 2km to and from school each day, and attended physical education classes. I also enjoyed skiing and swimming occasionally during the winter. This routine continued at ages 10 and 11, with the addition of a 1.7km route to school and extended weekly visits to the swimming pool. This passion for staying active stayed with me throughout my childhood.

In 2001 at age 12, I cycled my 7.8km school route a few times a year in warm weather, but mostly during summer to my friend's place 8.1km away. Outside of school, I did little exercise except for physical education classes and occasional skiing and swimming at the pool. This routine continued into the following year when I was 13.

During my teenage years, physical exercise wasn't a big part of my life. I would occasionally bike my school route of 7.8km and also visit my friends in Kiviniemi, which was 8.1km away. However, during school time I had very little free time for physical activity. We did have physical education classes and occasionally went skiing in the winter. I also went to the swimming hall by myself sometimes. Apart from that, I went to the gym with my cousin and his dad once a week for longer periods of time.

During my teenage years, physical exercise was not a significant part of my life. I would occasionally bike to and from school, as well as visit friends who lived about 8km away. However, due to school commitments, I had limited free time for physical activity. I did participate in physical education classes and occasional winter activities like skiing. Additionally, I would visit the swimming hall by myself and sometimes went to the gym with family once a week. The routine continued from ages 12 to 15.

From the ages of 8 to 15, physical exercise played an important role in my life. As a child from 1997-2000, I cycled or walked to school and attended physical education classes. I also enjoyed skiing and swimming during the winter. This routine continued until I was 11, with the addition of a longer route to school and weekly visits to the swimming pool. However, during my teenage years, school commitments limited my free time for physical activity. I still participated in physical education classes and occasional winter activities, but my routine was not as consistent as when I was younger. I would also make time to visit the swimming hall and occasionally go to the gym with family. Despite this, my passion for staying active stayed with me throughout my childhood and teenage years.

During my younger years, physical exercise played an important role in my life. From the age of 6, I would go skiing in the winter and visit the swimming pool, learning the value of staying fit. This routine continued until I was 11, with the addition of longer school routes and weekly pool visits. However, during my teenage years, school commitments limited my time for physical activity, although I still made time for physical education classes and occasional winter activities. My passion for staying active remained with me throughout my childhood and teenage years.

During my teenage years, I didn't prioritize physical exercise. I only cycled about 7.8km to school a few times a year, mostly during warm summer weather. Occasionally, I would bike 8.1km to visit my friends. Outside of school, I rarely made time for exercise. In physical education classes, we would do some activities but nothing too intense. I did get to go skiing a few times during the winter, but I hardly ever went to the swimming pool by myself after school.

In 2007, at the age of 18, I didn't prioritize exercise. While I cycled my 7.8km school route a few times a year, I rarely worked out otherwise. Physical education classes and occasional skiing were my main forms of activity.

One year later, at 19 years old, I started biking to school again, but only for 3km and eventually just 1km. My free time during school was also very inactive. However, I still had physical education classes at school.

During my teenage years, my personal taste for physical exercise was not a priority. I would only cycle a few times a year, mainly during the warm summer months, for a distance of about 7.8km to school or 8.1km to visit friends. Aside from these occasional bike rides, I rarely made time for exercise, even skipping the swimming pool after school. In physical education classes, we would engage in light activities, and I also had the opportunity to ski a few times during winter.

As I entered my late teens, my exercise habits remained largely unchanged. At 18 years old, I continued cycling my 7.8km school route periodically, but did not engage in any other form of activity. The following year, I started biking to school again, but for a shorter distance of only 3km, eventually reducing to just 1km. While my physical education classes at school provided some activity, my free time was mostly sedentary.

In 2009, at the age of 20, physical exercise was a small part of my routine. I mostly rode my bike to school and there were physical education classes. However, during basic training in the military, the level of physical activity increased, and even more so during my training as a Military Police Officer. We had tough exercises and had to wear heavy equipment, making it even more challenging.

The following year, as a group leader in the Military Police, I was part of a highly active company. We practiced more than any other company and had long exercises, often training outside in full gear. In my personal time, I also started going to the gym. This added an extra element to my physical activity routine and helped improve my overall fitness.

As I entered my early 20s, I realized the importance of regular physical activity for overall health and began incorporating activities like walking and cycling into my daily routine. value.text:
(Personal Taste Videogames, year 1994, age 5) Two games:
Jazz Jackrabbit
Sam & Max Hits The Road
Wolfenstein 3D
Commander Keen 4
Scorched Earth
Tunneler
Minebombers
Stunt Car Racer
Pizza Worm
<Some Unknown "Thrust" clone>
Slick'n'Slide

1995:

At the age of 6, I was already hooked on video games. Some of my favorites included Jazz Jackrabbit, Sam & Max Hits The Road, and Commander Keen 4. But I also enjoyed classics like Wolfenstein 3D, Scorched Earth, and Stunt Car Racer.

As a young gamer, I was also drawn to the simple yet addicting gameplay of games like Tunneler, Minebombers, and the lesser-known "Thrust" clone. And let's not forget the wacky racing fun of titles like Slick'n'Slide, Wacky Wheels, and One Must Fall. And of course, who could resist the hilarious adventures of the wise-cracking Earthworm Jim?

1996:

My love for gaming only continued to grow at the age of 7. On my Amiga 500, I spent hours racing in Stunt Car Racer, bouncing through levels in Parasol Stars, and popping bubbles in Bubble Bobble and Rainbow Islands.

But I also couldn't resist the charm of retro platformers like Giana Sisters and North vs South, or the strategic action of Worms and Speedball 1 & 2. And for some intense flying action, I turned to F/A-18 Interceptor and Formula One Grand Prix.

Plus, I always made sure to check out the latest releases at my local library. The Moomins games, Hide and Seek and On the Waves, were adorable and fun for any young gamer.

Overall, those were some of my favorite years of gaming, with highlights like virtual racing on the Megadrive and the absurdity of Ren & Stimpy: Stimpy's Invention.

In my early years of gaming, I couldn't get enough of titles like Jazz Jackrabbit, Sam & Max Hits The Road, and Commander Keen 4. The simple, addicting gameplay of games like Tunneler, Minebombers, and "Thrust" clones were also some of my favorites.

As I got older, I fell in love with games like Worms, Speedball 1 & 2, and Bubble Bobble on my Amiga 500. And I always made sure to check out the latest releases at my local library, like the adorable Moomins games and the absurdity of Ren & Stimpy: Stimpy's Invention.

But it wasn't just about the games themselves – I also had a blast playing with friends, whether it was in virtual racing on the Megadrive or the hilarious Earthworm Jim adventures. Video games truly were a big part of my childhood, and these were some of my most cherished memories.

(Personal Taste Videogames, from year 1993 to year 1996, age 4 - 7) In my early years of gaming, I couldn't get enough of titles like Jazz Jackrabbit, Sam & Max Hits The Road, and Commander Keen 4. The simple, addicting gameplay of games like Tunneler, Minebombers, and "Thrust" clones were also some of my favorites.

As I got older, I fell in love with games like Worms, Speedball 1 & 2, and Bubble Bobble on my Amiga 500. And I always made sure to check out the latest releases at my local library, like the adorable Moomins games and the absurdity of Ren & Stimpy: Stimpy's Invention.

But it wasn't just about the games themselves – I also had a blast playing with friends, whether it was in virtual racing on the Megadrive or the hilarious Earthworm Jim adventures. Video games truly were a big part of my childhood, and these were some of my most cherished memories.

Personal Taste Videogames, years 1997-1998, ages 8-9:
DOS games:
- Action Supercross

PC games:
- GTA 1

Amiga 500 games:
- Stunt Car Racer
- Parasol Stars
- Bubble Bobble
- Rainbow Islands
- Giana Sisters
- North vs South
- Worms
- Speedball 1 & 2
- Formula One Grand Prix
- Sensible Soccer
- F/A-18 Interceptor
- Fire and Ice

Children's games at the library:
- The Moomins: Moomins' Journey at Sea
- The Moomins: Hide and Seek

My personal taste in video games during my childhood in the late 90s and early 2000s was a mix of DOS, PC, Amiga 500, and PlayStation games. In 1999, at the age of 10, I enjoyed playing action-packed DOS games like "Action Supercross" and PC games like "Counter Strike beta" and "Unreal Tournament." I also had a collection of Amiga 500 games, including classics like "Bubble Bobble" and "Worms." As for PlayStation games, "Tony Hawk's Pro Skater 1" kept me entertained for hours.

The following year, at the age of 11, I continued my love for DOS with games like "The Incredible Machine" and "Wings." I also added "Kill Everyone 2" and "Kill Everyone 3" to my collection. On the PlayStation, I upgraded to "Tony Hawk's Pro Skater 2" and added "Colin McRae Rally" and "Spider Man." Meanwhile, on the PC, I played "GTA 2," "Half Life: Blue Shift," and "Elastomania."

Overall, my favorite games during this time were action-packed and fast-paced, with a mix of platformers, racing, and shooting games. They provided endless hours of fun and excitement, and I'll always look back on them with nostalgia.

From 1997 to 2000, ages 8 to 11, my personal taste in video games consisted of a variety of DOS, PC, Amiga 500, and PlayStation games. I loved action-packed titles like "Action Supercross," "GTA 1 and 2," and "Counter Strike beta." Classic games on Amiga 500, such as "Bubble Bobble" and "Worms," and newer ones like "Tony Hawk's Pro Skater" continually captivated me. As I grew older, my collection expanded to include titles like "The Incredible Machine," "Kill Everyone 2 and 3," and "Colin McRae Rally." These fast-paced games, from platformers to shooters, provided endless hours of enjoyment and nostalgia.

Year 2001-2002, Age 12-13: 
PC Games:
- Tony Hawk's Pro Skater 2

years.keywords: Family, Dog, Mixed breed, Finnish Spitz, Shy, Kids, Mom, Playing, High place, Injured, Leg, Sensitive, Rest of its life
years.native_text:
Perheeni hankki koiran nimeltä Nöpö. Se oli sekarotuinen, ja siinä oli suurin osa rodusta Suomen pystykorvaa.
Nöpö oli melko arka, ja me lapset tulimme liian lähelle, ja äitikään ei oikein osannut ajatella koirien parasta.
Leikimme Nöpön kanssa, ja se tippui melko korkealta, ja loukkasi jalan silleen, että se arasti sitä loppuelämänsä.
years.text:
My family got a dog named Nöpö. It was a mixed breed, with most of the breed being Finnish Spitz.
Nöpö was quite shy, and when we kids got too close, even our mom didn't always think about what was best for the dog.
We played with Nöpö and it fell from a pretty high place and injured its leg, causing it to be sensitive to it for the rest of its life.

years.keywords: Sister, Mother, I, Walking, Nöpö, Dog, Familiar, Nearby places, Gerbils, Escaped, Playing, Freely, Room, Dog instinct, Hunted, Killed
years.native_text:
Käytimme siskoni ja äitini kanssa Nöpö koiraa lenkillä vuorotellen useamman kerran päivässä.
Lähialueen paikat alkoivat tulla tutuiksi uudella tapaa.

Perheeni hankki siskolleni myös pieniä gerbiilejä, mutta leikkiessään vapaana huoneessa, ne pääsi vapaaksi, ja koiramme Nöpö vaiston varassa metsästi ja tappoi ne.
years.text:
My sister, my mother, and I took turns walking Nöpö the dog multiple times a day. We started to become familiar with the nearby places in a new way.

My family also got my sister some small gerbils, but when they were playing freely in the room, they escaped and our dog Nöpö instinctively hunted and killed them.

years.keywords: Sister 2. Mother 3. Dog 4. Walks 5. Annoyed 6. Cute 7. Sweet 8. Home alone 9. School 10. Stress 11. Worry 12. Late 13. Crying 14. Bike
years.native_text:
Käytimme siskoni ja äitini kanssa Nöpö koiraa lenkillä vuorotellen useamman kerran päivässä.
Minua jo harmitti hieman koiran omistaminen lenkittämisen takia.
Toisaalta, Nöpö oli tosi kiva ja suloinen aina.

Nöpö joutui olemaan päivät yksinään kotona, ja harmittelin sitä aina paljon.
Kerran kouluun lähtiessä Nöpö karkasi ulko-ovesta, ja jouduin juoksemaan hänen perässään pitkään.
Olin myöhässä sen jälkeen koulusta, mikä ei ollut tapaistani.
Itkin koko matkan, lähinnäkin Nöpön ja kiireen aiheuttaman stressin takia.
Taisin kaiken lisäksi kaatua pahasti pyörällä itkiessäni.
years.text:
My sister, mother and I took turns taking our dog Nöpö for walks several times a day.
I was starting to get a bit annoyed with having to walk the dog all the time.
But Nöpö was always so cute and sweet.

Nöpö had to stay home alone during the day, and it always made me feel bad for him.
One day, when I was leaving for school, Nöpö ran out of the front door and I had to chase after him for a long time.
I ended up being late for school, which was very unlike me.
I cried the whole way, mostly because of the stress and worry of Nöpö and being late.
I even fell off my bike while crying.

years.native_text:
Muutin ensimmäiseen omaan kotiin, ja myös ajauduin heti harmillisiin ongelmiin tahtomattani täysin muiden takia.
Tuli ikävä Nöpö koiraa, mutta rakastin myös omaa rauhaa.
Harmittaa hieman se, etten ottanut Nöpö hoitaan pitemmiksi ajoiksi.
Äitin joutui huolehtimaan täysin yksin Nöpöstä, eikä se enää saanut aivan riittävästi lenkitystä.
Onneksi äiti muutti taloon, missä oli melko paljon pihaa.
years.text:
I moved into my first own home, and also got caught up in unfortunate problems involuntarily due to others.
I missed my dog Nöpö, but I also loved having my own peace.
It's a bit regrettable that I didn't take care of Nöpö for longer periods of time.
My mother had to take care of Nöpö all by herself, and it didn't get enough walks anymore.
Luckily, my mother moved to a house with a fairly large yard.

years.keywords: Nöpö, quite often, not enough, enjoy, own peace, dog, nice
years.native_text: Näin Nöpöä edelleen melko usein, mutta en tarpeeksi. Toisaalta nautin omasta rauhastani, mutta koira on kiva.
years.text: I still see Nöpö quite often, but not enough. On the other hand, I enjoy my own peace, but the dog is nice.

Armeijassa en nähnyt Nöpö koiraa usein, ja sen jälkeen muutin Vaasaan.
Tänä vuonna näin hyvin vähän Nöpö-koiraa.
years.text:
I did not see Nöpö dog often in the army, and after that I moved to Vaasa.
This year I saw very little Nöpö dog.

years.native_text: Muutin takaisin Ouluun, ja Nöpö kävi silloin tällöin luonani. Minun olisi pitänyt ottaa se pitemmiksi ajoiksi, mutta edes äitini ei tajunnut ehdottaa tai ylipuhua minua siihen, vaikka se olisi ollut kaikkien kannalta parempi.
years.text: I moved back to Oulu, and Nöpö visited me from time to time. I should have taken it for longer periods, but even my mother did not think to suggest or persuade me to do so, even though it would have been better for everyone.

Näihin aikoihin Nöpö koiramme kuoli. Hänellä tuli melko paha kohtaus lopussa, ja hänet lopetettiin.
Nöpö jää sydämmeeni aina.
years.text:
Around this time our dog Nöpö passed away. He had a pretty bad episode towards the end, and he was put to sleep.
Nöpö will always be in my heart.

years.native_text:
Rudolf Steiner koulussa me harjoiteltiin lintujen tunnistamista, ja vihkoon piti tunnistaa kymmeniä lintuja. Silloin jouduin ensimmäisen kerran ottamaan vakavasti luonnon eläimet.
Epäonnistuin melko pahasti tässä tehtävässä, mutta kävimme kavereiden kanssa yrittämässä tosissaan lintujen näkemistä ennen deadlineä.
Tämä oli melko hauskaa, ja luulimme nähdeemme jotain harvinaisiakin lintuja, joita emme saaneet tunnistettua.
Opin melko paljon eri linnuista tässä vaiheessa.

Pidin silmät auki koiranulkoilutuslenkeillä eri tavalla tästä lähtien.
years.text:
At Rudolf Steiner school, we practiced recognizing birds and had to identify dozens of birds in our notebook. That was the first time I had to take nature and its animals seriously.
I failed quite miserably in this task, but my friends and I made a serious effort to spot birds before the deadline.
It was quite fun, and we even thought we saw some rare birds that we couldn't identify.
I learned a lot about different birds at this stage.

I started keeping a closer eye on my surroundings during dog walks after that.

years.keywords: university, lonely, feed, birds, forest, window, balcony, befriended, great tits, squirrels, communicate, gestures, scared, fell, second floor, ground, jumped down, grand gestures
years.native_text:
Olin melko yksinäinen yliopistossa, ja aloin ruokkimaan lintuja, koska ikkunani takana oli metsä ja minulla oli ikkunan takana tasanne.
Ystävystyin monien talitinttien ja oravien kanssa.

Opin puhumaan oravien kanssa eleillä hieman.
Ne mm. huomasivat, että säikähdin, kun he tippuivat toisesta kerroksesta maahan, jonka jälkeen he tulivat viereeni odottamaan, että varmasti katsoin, ja sitten se hyppäsi oikein suuri-eleisesti maahan asti.
years.text:
I was quite lonely at the university, and I started to feed the birds because there was a forest outside my window and I had a balcony outside the window.
I befriended many great tits and squirrels.

I learned to communicate with the squirrels through gestures.
They noticed that I got scared when they fell from the second floor to the ground, after which they came to me and waited until I looked, and then they jumped down with grand gestures.

years.keywords: new apartment, watch birds, ban, Great Tits, company, balcony, summer, solo hike, birds of nature, closer, first time, heard, early summer, racket, morning, wilderness, loud.
years.native_text:
Uudessa asunnossani en voinut vastustaa tilaisuutta lintuja kiellosta huolimatta.
Talitintit pitivät minulle usein seuraa syödessään parvekkeellani.

Kesällä aloin vaeltaa ensimmäisen kerran yksin, ja luonnon linnut tulivat minulle lähemmäs, kuin koskaan aikaisemmin.
Kuulin ensimmäistä kertaa alkukesäisen lintujen metelin aamulla keskellä luontoa, mikä on mielettömän kovaääninen.
years.text:
In my new apartment, I couldn't resist the opportunity to watch birds, despite the ban.
The Great Tits often kept me company as they ate on my balcony.

That summer, I ventured on my first solo hike, and the birds of nature came closer to me than ever before.
For the first time, I heard the early summer birds' racket in the morning, in the middle of the wilderness, which was incredibly loud.

years.text:
I watch birds in the winter and go on hikes in the summer.

During my summer hikes, I often observe many birds and try to communicate with them using whistles, which is sometimes successful.

(Animals Wild, from year 2017 to year 2020, age 28 - 31) Wild Animals, 2017-2020, age 28-31:
In my new apartment, despite the ban, I couldn't resist watching birds, particularly the Great Tits that often kept me company on my balcony. My first solo hike brought me closer to nature's birds than ever before, with their loud early summer chorus echoing through the wilderness.

During my time at university from 2005 to 2012, ages 16 to 23, I often felt lonely. To combat this, I began feeding the birds outside my window on my balcony which overlooked a forest. I formed bonds with various animals, particularly great tits and squirrels.

Through gestures, I even learned to communicate with the squirrels. They would purposely fall from the second floor and wait for me to see before jumping down with grand gestures.

After moving to a new place in 2013, ages 24 to 31, I couldn't resist watching and interacting with birds again, despite it being banned. On a solo hike, I was able to get even closer to nature's birds than ever before, listening to their vibrant chorus in the wilderness.

From 1989 to 2004, ages 0 to 15, I was captivated by Animals Wild, learning about nature's creatures through books and encounters with birds and small animals on walks. My time at Rudolf Steiner school introduced me to the joys of spotting and identifying different bird species.

Years passed and I found solace in feeding birds on my balcony during university. I formed bonds with great tits and squirrels, even learning to communicate with them through gestures. In 2013, aged 24 to 31, I couldn't resist interacting with birds on a solo hike, experiencing their vibrant chorus in the wilderness.

In the wild, I love observing birds year-round. In the winter, I watch them closely, while in the summer, I embark on hikes and wanderings to listen to their singing. I even try to communicate with them using whistles, sometimes with success. Recently, I've also started taking trips closer to home to listen to the loud spring birds.

Animals in the Wild, 2023-2024, 34-35 years:
Squirrels, Birds

From 2021 to 2022, aged 32-33, I love observing birds year-round in the wild. In winter, I watch them closely, and in summer, I hike and listen to their singing, sometimes communicating with them using whistles. Recently, I also take trips closer to home to listen to loud spring birds. In 2023-2024, aged 34-35, I continue my love for animals in the wild, focusing on observing squirrels and birds.

Pelasimme paljon pelejä, jotka Ollin isoveli oli asettanut pikanäppäinten taakse.
Meidän tarvitsi vain käynnistää kone, painaa numeroa, ja enter.
Pelejä oli mm.:
- Jazz Jackrabbit
- Sam & Max Hits the Road
- Rampart
- Minebombers
- Scorched Earth
- some cave flying game, which I can't find from any archives
- Pizza Worm
- Wolfenstein 3D
- Stunt Car Racer
- Slick 'n' Slide

Olin Ollin luona yökylässä usein, ja pelasimme pelejä pitkälle yöhön.
years.text:
My best friend Olli-Pekka Aaltonen had a PC with DOS and an Intel 386 processor.
More specifically, it was a genuine IBM XT with an Intel Inboard 386.
We played a lot of games, which Olli's older brother had set up with quick keys.
All we had to do was start the computer, press a number, and hit enter.
Some of the games were:
- Jazz Jackrabbit
- Sam & Max Hits the Road
- Rampart
- Minebombers
- Scorched Earth
- some cave flying game, which I can't find from any archives
- Pizza Worm
- Wolfenstein 3D
- Stunt Car Racer
- Slick 'n' Slide

I often stayed overnight at Olli's place, playing games until late in the night.

years.native_text:
Koulussani oli PC tietokoneita, joissa oli Windows 3.11 ja opetuspelejä.
Kirjastossamme oli lapsille tarkoitettuja PC:eitä, joilla sai pelata kilttejä lasten pelejä.

Halusin tietokoneen tai pelikonsolin kotia, jolloin äitini bongasi Amiga 500:sen myynti-ilmoituksen.
Se oli mahtava laite, ja meillä oli 100 peliä sille disketeillä.
Siitä riitti iloa vuosiksi.
Parhaita pelejä oli:
- Parasol Stars, jota pelasin siskoni kanssa (onneksi meidän kräkätyssä versiossa oli loputtomien elämien trainer)
- Bubble Bobble
- South vs North
- many many more
years.text:
There were PC computers with Windows 3.11 and educational games in my school.
Our library had PCs meant for children, where they could play nice games.

I wanted a computer or a game console for our house, and that's when my mother spotted a sale ad for an Amiga 500.
It was an awesome device, and we had 100 games for it on floppy disks.
It brought us joy for years.
Some of the best games were:
- Parasol Stars, which I played with my sister (luckily our cracked version had an endless lives trainer)
- Bubble Bobble
- South vs North
- many many more

years.text:
My mother bought a brand new computer for our home, which had:
- 480MHz AMD processor
- Riva TNT2 graphics card
- 20gb hard drive space
- 64mb memory
- large 17" monitor
- printer
- sound card and speakers
- 56k modem

Our family friend Pekka Kähkönen helped us a lot and organized the computer purchase. He taught me a lot about using the computer and is still a good friend of mine.

I got 3 games with the computer:
- GTA 2
- Supreme Snowboarding
- Driver

I played them a lot and they provided comfort for me during a difficult social situation at school.

I also played Counter Strike beta and Unreal Tournament at my friend's house in LAN parties and tried to get it to work on my new computer, but I couldn't due to the copy protection.

With the new computer, my sister and I also played Game Boy Color Pokemon games through an emulator.

value.text:
(Home Computer, year 1993, age 4) My best friend Olli-Pekka Aaltonen had a PC with DOS and an Intel 386 processor.
More specifically, it was a genuine IBM XT with an Intel Inboard 386.
We played a lot of games, which Olli's older brother had set up with quick keys.
All we had to do was start the computer, press a number, and hit enter.
Some of the games were:
- Jazz Jackrabbit
- Sam & Max Hits the Road
- Rampart
- Minebombers
- Scorched Earth
- some cave flying game, which I can't find from any archives
- Pizza Worm
- Wolfenstein 3D
- Stunt Car Racer
- Slick 'n' Slide

I often stayed overnight at Olli's place, playing games until late in the night.

In 1995, I was just 6 years old and my friend Olli-Pekka's new IBM laptop was the coolest thing ever. We played the Across motorcycle racing game for hours. But that wasn't the only place for gaming - at my friend Tuomas Ruokamo's house, we played classics like Wacky Wheels, Doom, and Duke Nukem 3D. At my cousin Keijo Pakonen's house, it was all about Commander Keen 4 and the Windows games.

The following year, I turned 7 and gaming became more accessible. My school had PC computers with educational games and our library had special ones for kids. But even then, I still wanted my own computer or game console. Luckily, my mom found a sale ad for an Amiga 500 and it changed our lives. We had 100 games on floppy disks and some of the best were Parasol Stars, Bubble Bobble, and South vs North. The Amiga 500 brought us joy for years to come.

The age of 4 was a major turning point for me when my best friend Olli-Pekka Aaltonen introduced me to his PC with an Intel 386 processor. We spent countless hours playing games like Jazz Jackrabbit and Wolfenstein 3D, and I often stayed over at his place to continue our gaming marathon into the late night.

Then, at the age of 6, Olli-Pekka got a new IBM laptop and we were hooked on the motorcycle racing game Across. But our gaming adventures didn't stop there - at my friend Tuomas Ruokamo's house, we played classics like Doom and Duke Nukem 3D, while my cousin Keijo Pakonen's place was all about Commander Keen 4 and Windows games.

As I turned 7, gaming became more accessible through my school's educational PC games and the library's special kids' games. But my love for gaming truly blossomed when my mom found a sale ad for an Amiga 500, sporting 100 games on floppy disks. Parasol Stars, Bubble Bobble, and South vs North were just a few of the gems that brought us endless joy for years to come.

(Home Computer, year 1999, age 10) My mother bought a brand new computer for our home, which had:
- 480MHz AMD processor
- Riva TNT2 graphics card
- 20gb hard drive space
- 64mb memory
- large 17" monitor
- printer
- sound card and speakers
- 56k modem

Our family friend Pekka Kähkönen helped us a lot and organized the computer purchase. He taught me a lot about using the computer and is still a good friend of mine.

I got 3 games with the computer:
- GTA 2
- Supreme Snowboarding
- Driver

I played them a lot and they provided comfort for me during a difficult social situation at school.

I also played Counter Strike beta and Unreal Tournament at my friend's house in LAN parties and tried to get it to work on my new computer, but I couldn't due to the copy protection.

With the new computer, my sister and I also played Game Boy Color Pokemon games through an emulator.

Lapsuudenkodissani syötiin aina terveellisesti. Usein oli puuroa, mutta luonnonjugurtti, mysli ja hunaja olivat yksi tavallisimmista aamupaloistani.
Keittiö oli iso ja tilava lapsen näkökulmasta.
Muistan kuinka äitini paistoi kesäisin pannukakkua, jossa oli paljon nokkosta.
years.text:
In my childhood home, we always ate healthy. There was often porridge, but natural yoghurt, muesli, and honey were one of my most common breakfasts.
The kitchen was big and spacious from a child's perspective.
I remember how my mother used to make nettle pancakes in the summertime.

I only had a small kitchenette, but it had everything I needed.
I moved the quiet, yet annoying fridge to the hallway, where it didn't cause any noise issues.
The kitchen furniture was very old and a bit problematic, but I didn't let it bother me.
The good aspects of the apartment, such as large windows and a garden on the first floor, made up for the bad kitchen.

Perustin myös suomi-hiphop bändin nimeltä PMS, myöhemmin Pohjantähti, mitä bändikaverini yritti kierosti omia omaksi henkilökohtaiseksi projektikseen.

years.text:
We disbanded our band The Wayward because of disagreements. I started a new band called The Vice.
I also started a Finnish hip-hop band called PMS, later renamed Pohjantähti, which my bandmate attempted to take over as his personal project in a sneaky way.

After our first show, we ended The Vice on a high note. It felt like I had been carrying a dead weight with me.

years.keywords: Trip, Oldest friend, Olli-Pekka, Summer, Oulu, Helsinki, Stockholm, Linnanmaa amusement park, Walking, City, Tourist attractions, Music, Steinberg Cubase, Mikko, MobileMese, Visual Basic, Nokia, Symbian OS, MSN, Linux, Mandrake Linux, Second computer, Discarded components, Funds.
years.native_text:
Kävin kesällä vanhimman kaverini Olli-Pekan kanssa matkalla kahdestaan. Menimme Oulusta Helsinkiin, Helsingistä Tukholmaan, ja Tukholmasta Ouluun.
Kuljimme keskenään Linnanmaan huvipuistossa, kaupungilla ja turistikohteissa.
Aloitin tällä reissulla tekemään musiikkia ammattimaisella Steinberg Cubase ohjelmistolla, kiitos Olli-Pekan isoveljen Mikon.

Tein "MobileMese" ohjelmaa Visual Basicilla Nokia puhelimelle ja Symbian käyttöjärjestelmälle, millä pystyi käyttämään MSN:ää. Ohjelma kirjautui sisään ja latasi onnistuneesti kaverilistan, mutta oli muilta osin puutteellinen.

Opettelin käyttämään Linux käyttöjärjestelmää. Asensin Madrake Linux 9.2:n kakkostietokoneelleni, minkä olin köyhänä kasannut vanhoista ja hylätyistä komponenteista.
years.text:
I went on a trip with my oldest friend Olli-Pekka during the summer. We traveled from Oulu to Helsinki, then from Helsinki to Stockholm, and finally back to Oulu.
We spent time together at the Linnanmaa amusement park, walking around the city, and visiting tourist attractions.
During this trip, I started making music using the professional Steinberg Cubase software, thanks to Olli-Pekka's older brother Mikko.

I also created a program called "MobileMese" using Visual Basic for Nokia phones and the Symbian operating system, which allowed me to use MSN. The program successfully logged in and loaded my friend list, but was lacking in other aspects.

I also learned how to use the Linux operating system. I installed Mandrake Linux 9.2 on my second computer, which I had put together using old and discarded components while I was still low on funds.

I founded the Finnish hip-hop project PMS, and our first song "Sydämen Asialla" was at the top of the Mikseri.net charts for several weeks. I had composed, written and produced the song.

Estin tyttöystävääni tappamasta itseään vajaa 10 kertaa, minkä johtui hänen käyttämistään ilmaisista huumeista, traumaattisista kotioloista ja minun halusta erota.
Kävin koulussa täysin säännöllisesti ja täydellä voimalla kaikista minuun kohdistuvista negatiivisista paineista huolimatta.

years.text:
I stayed strong when my girlfriend had mental health issues caused by her new drug-using classmates offering her free drugs. I prevented her from attempting suicide almost 10 times, due to her use of these free drugs, traumatic home situation, and my desire to break up.
I attended school regularly and with full force, despite all the negative pressures directed at me.

I release my first full album for my Finnish hip-hop project, with one track featuring Sana (Sanna Rönberg) becoming highly popular on mikseri.net.

I travel to London, UK for 3 weeks. I explore London and its surroundings with my friend by car. Every day, we go somewhere new by car.

Suojauduin pahoinpitelyssä juuri riittävästi säilyttääkseni näköni oikeassa silmässä.
Pysyn vahvana ja optimistisena, vaikka pahoinpitelystä naamaani tulee 15cm arpea ja otsassani on arvet kuten Harry Potterilla.

years.text:
I am dating new beautiful girls. I act smart when someone is not interested.
I had my first successful one-night stand.
I protected myself well enough during a physical assault to keep my vision in my right eye.
I remain strong and optimistic, even though I have a 15cm scar on my face and scars on my forehead like Harry Potter.

I am touring with my third metal band several times. The band mostly plays my songs. I play electric guitar in the band.

I am acting in a long play and performing in multiple shows.

I am going on a 2-week interrail trip to Germany, Czech Republic, Austria and Italy.

years.keywords: Gig, Metal band, Oulu Teatria, High school, Graduated, Good grades, Army, Basic training, Positive team spirit, Military police, Non-commissioned officer school, Health, Officer candidate school, Service, Survival, Rigorous, Rovaniemi, Challenging conditions, Field exercise, Temperature, Tents, Guard duty, Relationship, Budding, December 2009, Sleep, Endured, Daily tasks, Responsibilities
years.native_text:
Teen isoimman keikkani metallibändini kanssa. Yleisössä on yli 300 henkeä ja paikkana on Oulun Teatria.

Kirjoitin ylioppilaaksi hyvin arvosanoin.

Menin armeijaan.
Pidin yllä hyvää yhteishenkeä armeijan alokasaikana.
Menin sotilaspoliisi aliupseerikouluun.
Päätin puolustaa terveyttäni, ja jättää pois AUK:in, vaikka halusinkin. AUK:iin meneminen olisi luultavasti katkaissut koko palvelukseni jostain kohtaa.
Selvisin erittäin tiukasta sotilaspoliisi-aliupseerikoulusta Rovaniemellä.

Kestin haastavissa oloissa. Joulukuussa 2009 olin yli viikon leirillä, missä pakkasta oli -25, ja olimme teltassa. Vartiovuoroni kesti yhteensä jopa 8 tuntia päivässä.

Minulla oli orastava seurustelusuhde.
years.text:
This was my biggest gig with my metal band. There were over 300 people in the audience and it took place at Oulu Teatria.

I graduated with good grades from high school.

I joined the army.
I maintained a positive team spirit during my basic training.
I went to military police non-commissioned officer school.
I decided to prioritize my health and skip the officer candidate school, even though I wanted to go. Going to that school would have probably cut my service short at some point.
I survived the very rigorous military police non-commissioned officer course in Rovaniemi.

I endured challenging conditions. In December 2009, I was on a field exercise for over a week where the temperature was -25 degrees Celsius and we slept in tents. My guard duty lasted up to 8 hours a day.

I had a budding relationship.

years.keywords: Defense, Unknown, Conspiracy, Successful, Calm, Decision, Toxicity, Tsunami, Framed, Crime, Protect, Best friend, Reputation, Future career, Doctor, Ruined, Cool, Accepted, University, Oulu, Study, Environmental Engineering, Personal need, Sacrifice, Others.
years.native_text:
Hankin monta sataa Facebook kaveria ensimmäisen vuosipuoliskon aikana.
Lisäsin vanhoja Kiimingin aikaisia kavereita ja juttelin heidän kanssaan.
Selvisin todella haastavissa oloissa vuoden palvelusajan loppuun.
Minua kohtaa juoniteltiin "in your face" salaliitolla armeijassa, mutta kestin sen vahvana.

Huomasin bändini jäsenten olevan verkostoituneita "in your face" salaliittolaisiin myös, joten päätin lopettaa sen ihmissuhteen. Ikävä en voinut potkia viittä ihmistä pois bändistäni, joten päätin lähteä, ja bändi hajosi perässäni. Kukaan ei onneksi yrittänyt vallata minulle kuuluvaa Intellectual Propertyä. Katkaisin nämä toksiset ihmissuhteet onnistuneesti.


Vartioin suomen puolustusvoimien Hornet hävittäjiä viikon.

Pääsin Vaasan yliopistoon lukemaan Sähkötekniikkaa.

Aloin käyttämään Linux työpöytää ensisijaisena työpöytänä. Distrona oli Ubuntu ja Debian.
years.text:
I added over a hundred Facebook friends during the first half of the year. I reconnected with old friends from my hometown Kiiminki and had conversations with them. I managed to survive the challenging conditions of my year of service. There was a "in your face" plot against me in the army, but I stayed strong.

I noticed that some members of my band were also connected to the "in your face" conspirators, so I decided to end that relationship. Unfortunately, I couldn't kick five people out of my band, so I decided to leave instead, and the band broke up with me. Thankfully, no one tried to take ownership of my intellectual property. I successfully cut off these toxic relationships.

I guarded the Finnish Defense Forces' Hornet fighters for a week.

I got accepted to study Electrical Engineering at the University of Vaasa.

I started using Linux as my primary operating system. I used Ubuntu and Debian distros.

After years, I started making music again for my own taste and needs.

Kävin onnistunutta puolustustaistelua tuntematonta "in your face" salaliittoa minua kohtaan. Ongelman luonne oli vaikea, ja sen syy oli tuntematon. Tein onnistuneen kylmänrauhallisen ratkaisun poistua Facebookista ylivoimaisen toksisuuden tsunamin tullessa vastaan.

Pysyin vahvana, kun minut lavastettiin rikoksesta liittyen "in your face" salaliittoon minua vastaan, ja suojasin onnistuneesti parhaan kaverini maineen, jonka tuleva lääkärin työura olisi kärsinyt merkittävästi tai kariutunut kokonaan, jos pokkani ei olisi pitänyt.

Pääsin Oulun yliopistoon lukemaan Ympäristötekniikkaa.

Seurasin omaa henkilökohtaista tarvettani enkä uhrautunut muiden tarpeille.

Aloin ohjelmoimaan pitkän tauon jälkeen. Kielenä muutaman viikon Perl, mikä vaihtui standardi C++:ksi, ja sitten nopeasti Ultimate++ C++ frameworkiksi.

Selittämättömien vaikeuksieni seurauksena kirjoittin yksityiskohtaista päiväkirjaa, mikä selkeytti ajatuksiani ja auttoi ratkaisemaan ongelmiani vahvasti.

Tein vuosien jälkeen uudestaan musiikkia omaan makuuni ja omiin tarpeisiini.
years.text:
I successfully defended myself against an unknown "in your face" conspiracy targeted at me. The problem was complex and its cause was unknown. I made a calm and successful decision to remove myself from Facebook when faced with an overwhelming wave of toxicity.

I remained strong when I was framed for a crime related to the "in your face" conspiracy against me, and successfully protected the reputation of my best friend, whose future career as a doctor would have been significantly affected or completely ruined if I had not kept my cool.

I got accepted to study Environmental Engineering at the University of Oulu.

I followed my own personal needs and did not sacrifice myself for the needs of others.

I started programming again after a long break. I used Perl for a few weeks before switching to standard C++, and then eventually to the Ultimate++ C++ framework.

value.text:
(Badge Of Honor, year 1994, age 5) I played Wolfenstein 3D shareware maps through. I did fast lap in Stunt Car Racer game (for DOS). I played Jazz Jackrabbit very well.
I was very good against others in Scorched Earth and that tunneling tank game.
I got relatively far in Sam & Max Hit the Road game.

When I was six years old in 1995, Aleksanteri Ahola-Valo taught me to read with plastic letters in Tampere. He was a kind and patient teacher.

The following year, at age seven, I excelled in math, writing, and reading and received the smiley boy award. I also learned how to use the DOS prompt and play 100 different Amiga 500 games, despite not understanding the English language. Through trial and error, I mastered the menus and game logic. It was a fun and challenging experience.

From age 4 to 7, I proudly wore my Badge of Honor. In 1994, at age 5, I conquered Wolfenstein 3D and dominated Stunt Car Racer and Jazz Jackrabbit. I also excelled in Scorched Earth and a tank game. The next year, Aleksanteri Ahola-Valo patiently taught me to read using plastic letters in Tampere. And at age 7, I received the smiley boy award for my excellence in math, writing, and reading. In addition, I conquered the DOS prompt and mastered 100 Amiga 500 games, despite not knowing English. It was a challenging and enjoyable experience.

(Badge Of Honor, from year 1993 to year 1996, age 4 - 7) From age 4 to 7, I proudly wore my Badge of Honor. In 1994, at age 5, I conquered Wolfenstein 3D and dominated Stunt Car Racer and Jazz Jackrabbit. I also excelled in Scorched Earth and a tank game. The next year, Aleksanteri Ahola-Valo patiently taught me to read using plastic letters in Tampere. And at age 7, I received the smiley boy award for my excellence in math, writing, and reading. In addition, I conquered the DOS prompt and mastered 100 Amiga 500 games, despite not knowing English. It was a challenging and enjoyable experience.

At the age of 8 in 1997, I conquered my fear and learned to ski, enjoying it so much that even a week-long camping trip in Lapland's Karigasniemi region, including a 25km hike through canyons and mountains, didn't faze me. The following year, at 9 years old, I took second place in a school skiing competition and devoured books from the library while listening to music on borrowed CDs. Despite facing sexual harassment and discrimination, I remained strong and positive, even in the face of my friends' shiny new Sony PlayStation, while all I had was an Amiga 500.

At age 10, I wore my Badge of Honor as I faced discrimination, harassment, and isolation in a moldy school. But I stayed strong, finding solace in books and the internet despite having no friends. A year later, I moved and changed schools, leaving behind my past troubles. With newfound friends, my mental state improved, proving my resilience and determination.

From conquering my fear of skiing at 8 years old to facing discrimination and isolation in school at age 10, I refused to let any obstacle bring me down. Despite the challenges, I excelled in a skiing competition and found solace in books and the internet. And at 11 years old, I moved to a new school, proving my resilience and determination. My Badge of Honor shines through it all.

At the age of 12, I bravely chose to switch schools, leaving behind new friends but maintaining a positive attitude. I also took on a lead role in a long play and performed in multiple shows.

The following year, at age 13, I shifted my focus to making music on my computer instead of playing games. I also taught myself programming using online tutorials and created a variety of programs. These experiences have shaped me into a determined and multi-talented individual.

In 2003, at 14 years old, my oldest friend Olli-Pekka and I went on a memorable summer trip from Oulu to Helsinki, Stockholm, and back. We explored the city, visited tourist attractions, and had a blast at the Linnanmaa amusement park. The highlight of the trip was when Olli-Pekka's brother Mikko introduced me to making music on Steinberg Cubase.

The following year, at 15, I ventured into the world of programming and created "MobileMese," a program for Nokia phones that allowed me to use MSN. I also learned how to use the Linux operating system and installed Mandrake Linux 9.2 on my second computer.

But my biggest achievement that year was getting my first kiss and ending up in multiple relationships after playing a truth or dare game with a group of girls. And to top it all off, I hiked a 3-night hike in Lapland's UKK National Park with my friends. These experiences truly earned me my badge of honor.

From the ages of 12 to 15, I constantly pushed myself to try new things and expand my skills. At 12, I left behind old friends to switch schools, and at 13, I immersed myself in music and programming. At 14, I went on an unforgettable summer trip and discovered my love for making music on Steinberg Cubase. The following year, at 15, I delved into programming and created my own program for Nokia phones, while also exploring the world of Linux. I also shared my first kiss and went on a memorable hike with friends in Lapland's UKK National Park. These experiences have shaped me into a determined and multi-talented individual, earning me my badge of honor.

My Badge of Honor spans from age 8 to 15, reflecting my unwavering determination and resilience through various challenges. From overcoming fear and discrimination, to excelling in skiing and finding solace in my passions, I refused to be held back. At 11, I proved my adaptability by moving schools, and from 12 to 15, I continuously pushed myself in music, programming and creating my own software. These experiences have shaped me into a multi-talented and determined individual, earning me my badge of honor.

From the ages of 4 to 15, I proudly wore my Badge of Honor. In my early years, I conquered video games and learned to read with the help of a patient teacher. By age 7, I had received an award for my academic achievements. As I got older, I faced challenges head on and refused to be held back. From moving schools to pursuing my passions, I showed my adaptability and determination. My Badge of Honor represents my resilience and unwavering spirit, shaping me into a multi-talented individual.

At 16, I became more social and enjoyed evenings drinking wine with friends. I also took up electric guitar, using the Guitar Pro software to learn. With my classmate, I formed a metal band called The Wayward. The following year, at 17, I founded another metal band and led it to our first performance.

But music wasn't my only passion - I also started a rap project and our song "Sydämen Asialla" became a hit with 50,000 listens. Meanwhile, I also began dating my girlfriend and learned about sex and different techniques.

At 18 years old, I proved my strength by supporting my girlfriend through her struggles with mental health and preventing her from attempting suicide multiple times. Despite negative pressures, I excelled in school and released my first album for my Finnish hip-hop project. I also had the opportunity to explore London with a friend for 3 weeks.

The following year, at 19 years old, I showed my maturity by handling rejection gracefully and experiencing my first one-night stand. I also showed physical resilience during a physical assault, despite being left with scars.

I continued to pursue my passions by touring with my third metal band, performing in multiple shows, and acting in a long play. Additionally, I embarked on a 2-week interrail trip to several European countries and used Linux as my primary desktop.

Not only did I expand my horizons by reading about world politics on the zerohedge website, but I also learned to see things from different global perspectives. Despite facing challenges, I remained strong and took on new experiences with optimism and determination.

From my teenage years through my early twenties, I faced challenges that tested my strength, resilience, and maturity.

At 16, I delved into music, forming a metal band and learning guitar. But music wasn't my only passion - I also started a successful rap project. At 18, I supported my girlfriend through her struggles with mental health while excelling in school and releasing my first album. The following year, I explored London and faced rejection and physical assault, but remained resilient.

Despite these challenges, I never stopped pursuing my passions - touring with my metal band, acting in a long play, and embarking on a 2-week trip across Europe. I also expanded my horizons through reading and learning to see things from different global perspectives.

Through it all, I remained optimistic and determined, always pushing forward with a badge of honor.

In 2009 at age 20, I had a defining moment when my metal band played a sold-out show for over 300 people at Oulu Teatria. I also graduated high school with good grades and joined the army, where I maintained a positive team spirit and completed a rigorous non-commissioned officer course. Despite facing tough conditions, including sleeping in -25 degree weather during a field exercise, I prioritized my health and decided not to attend officer candidate school. years.native_text:
Koulussa liikuntasalissa oli joku valinnainen tapahtuma, mutta minä jäin mielummin tietokoneluokkaan.
Olin hieman piilossa luokassa, ja näin kun kaksi opettajaa suutelevat ja kähmivät toisiaan opettajan pöydän luona.
Säikähdin ja vaivihkaa hiivin heidän ohi pois luokasta.
Menin jokseenkin paniikkiin turhaan, koska elin vain siskon ja yksinhuoltajaäidin luona, eli kotona ei näkynyt mitään rakkauden eleitä koskaan, joten se oli outoa senkin takia.


Jouduin kerran ongelmiin, mikä ei ollut tapojeni mukaista.
Liikuntasalissa oli salibandy-kilpailu, ja meidän piti olla katsomassa.
Kaverini kanssa turhauduttiin ja heitettiin typerää vitsiä, ja päätettiin buuata peliin.
Jouduimme siitä opettajan puhutteluun.
years.text:
There was some optional event in the school gym, but I would rather stay in the computer lab.
I was hiding in the classroom, and I saw two teachers kissing and groping each other at the teacher's desk.
I got scared and quietly sneaked past them and left the room.
I panicked unnecessarily, because I only lived with my sister and single mother, so there were never any displays of affection at home, which made it even stranger.


I once got in trouble, which was not typical of me.
There was a floorball competition in the gym, and we were supposed to watch.
My friend and I got frustrated and made silly jokes, and we decided to boo the game.
We were called in by the teacher to talk about it.

years.native_text:
Muutimme perhetuttuni Pekka Kähkösen lähelle, joka oli auttanut meidän perhettä ensimmäisen PC:n hankkimisessa.
Aloin käymään hänen luona kylässä, etenkin koska hänellä oli nopea internet, ja minulla ei enää ollut kirjastoa lähellä, jossa käydä tietokoneella internetissä vapaasti.
Hän myös näytti kaikenlaista mielenkiintoista internetissä ja poltti minulle cd-levyillä ohjelmia.
Hän myös antoi minulle Windows XP cd-levyn asennuksen, jossa oli kuuluisa FCKGW serial, jonka minäkin opin muistamaan ulkoa, kuten internet meemissä kuuluu :)
Pilasin monta perheemme tietokoneen Windows 98 ja XP asennusta näillä kokeiluillani, mutta tietokoneilla ei säilytetty siihen aikaan omia tiedostoja ja kirjanmerkkejä juurikaan.
Puhuimme Pekan kanssa silloin tällöin myös ohjelmoinnista, mikä ylläpiti kiinnostustani.
years.text:
We moved near my family acquaintance Pekka Kähkönen, who had helped our family purchase our first PC.
I started visiting him often, especially because he had fast internet and I no longer had a library nearby where I could use the computer and internet freely.
He also showed me all sorts of interesting things on the internet and burned programs onto CDs for me.
He even gave me a Windows XP installation CD with the famous FCKGW serial number, which I also memorized by heart like in the internet meme :)
I messed up many of our family's Windows 98 and XP installations with my experiments, but at that time computers didn't really store personal files and bookmarks.
Pekka and I also talked about programming from time to time, which kept my interest alive.

years.keywords: Pekka Kähkönen, Programming Tunnel, Visual Basic, CD, burned, instructions, proficient, hundreds of hours, small programs, download, text files, internet, parse, important information, technique, everyday life, 20 years later, programmers, good or bad, outgrowing, MobileMese, client program, MSN Messenger, add-on, Nokia phones, dream
years.native_text:
Luultavasti perhetuttavani Pekka Kähkönen antoi vihjeen ohjelmointiputka nimiselle sivustolle, jossa oli Visual Basic tutoriaaleja.
Sain häneltä luultavasti Visual Basic 6:sen poltetulla cd-levyllä.
Aloin seuraamaan ohjeita ohjelmointiputkassa, ja opin Visual Basicin hyvin.
Käytin Visual Basic ohjelmointiin paljon aikaa, satoja tunteja vuodessa.

Muistan tekemistäni Visual Basic ohjelmistani pienet ohjelmat, jotka latasivat internetistä tekstitiedostoja, ja sitten parsivat sieltä jotain oleellista tietoa.
Tämä oli tekniikka, jota käytän vielä 20 vuotta myöhemmin arkisesti, ja johon en ole vieläkään saanut kommentteja muilta ohjelmoijilta, että kuinka hyvä tai huono kyseinen tekniikka on, mutta ainakin se toimii.

Muistan myös viimeisen ohjelman, jonka tein, kunnes "kasvoin yli" VisualBasicistä.
Kyseessä oli "MobileMese" niminen ohjelma, joka oli asikasohjelma MSN Messengerille.
Se käytti Visual Basicille luotua lisäosaa, mikä mahdollisti Visual Basic ohjelmien kirjoittamisen Nokian puhelimille.
Minulla ei siltikään ollut puhelinta, jolla oikeasti kokeilla kyseistä ohjelmaa, mutta unelma eli.
years.text:
My family acquaintance, Pekka Kähkönen, probably gave me a tip about a website called "Programming Tunnel" where there were tutorials for Visual Basic.
I probably got Visual Basic 6 from him on a burned CD.
I started following the instructions on Programming Tunnel and became very proficient in Visual Basic.
I spent a lot of time, hundreds of hours a year, programming in Visual Basic.

I remember the small programs I made using Visual Basic, which would download text files from the internet and then parse out some important information.
This was a technique that I still use in my everyday life 20 years later, and I have yet to receive any comments from other programmers on how good or bad this technique may be, but at least it works.

I also remember the last program I made before "outgrowing" Visual Basic.
It was called "MobileMese" and was a client program for MSN Messenger.
It used an add-on created for Visual Basic, which allowed for writing Visual Basic programs for Nokia phones.
I still didn't have a phone to actually try out the program, but the dream lived on.

years.native_text:
Armeijassa kuulin motivoivia tarinoita, jotka vaikuttivat innostumiseeni ohjelmoinnista uudelleen. Tarinoissa tykkien kohteet laskettiin tietokoneella, joiden ohjelmoinnista joillakin skappareilla oli tarinoita, mitä he jakoivat.
Menin yliopistoon armeijan takia, mikä vaikutti ohjelmoinnin uudelleenaloittamiseen, mutta vielä tänäkin vuonna keskityin täysin musiikin tuottamiseen, enkä ohjelmoinut ollenkaan.
years.text:
In the army, I heard motivational stories that influenced my renewed interest in programming. In these stories, cannon targets were calculated using computers and some of the officers had stories to share about their programming experiences.
I went to university because of the army, which also influenced my decision to start programming again. However, even this year I focused entirely on producing music and didn't do any programming.

years.native_text:
Muutin tänä vuonna takaisin kotikaupunkiini, ja innostuin ohjelmoimisesta uudelleen.
Aloitin ohjelmoimisen uudelleen perl-ohjelmointikielellä.

Miksi valitsin Perl:in Pythonin ja muiden sijaan? En ole varma. Minulle suositeltiin yliopistokaverini toimesta Pythonia, mutta olin varma, että en halua sillä ohjelmoida.
Perl liittyi jotenkin ubuntu työpöydän käyttöön ja aikaisempaan Visual Basic kokemukseeni intuitiivisesti. Olin kyllä nähnyt eri ohjelmointikieli-vaihtoehtoja jo vuosia linuxissa.



Jayno.pl: 29.9.2011
	Tämä on ensimmäisiä ohjelmia, mitä kirjoitin linux ympäristössä koskaan.
	Ohjelma käyttää GTK2 ikkunaa ja Glade:llä suunnitteltua käyttöliittymää.
	Se ottaa käyttäjältä hakusanan ja hakee sen googlesta.
	Kun google palauttaa tuloksen, sen url kirjoitetaan gui:hin.
	En muista, että ohjelma olisi koskaan toiminut.
	Nyt kun luen koodia, ja ymmärrän perl:iä, vaikken ole sitä tämän jälkeen ohjelmoinutkaan, niin huomaan, että tässä on muutama kyseenalainen kohta.

pallotaustakuva.pl: 5.10.2011
	Tämä ohjelma on käytännössä shell-skripti, mutta perl:issä.
	Se hakee osoitteesta "fourmilab.ch/cgi-bin/Earth" kuvan suomen yläpuolelta taustakuvaksi.

graphviz.pl: 6.10.2011
	Tässä ohjelmassa tehdään graafi, missä on pallojen sisällä tekstiä, ja pallot on yhdistetty kiemuraisilla viivoilla ja nuolilla.
	Pallot, eli nodet, on paikkoja, missä olen asunut.
	Pallot yhdistetään siten, miten muutin paikasta toiseen.

asennus.txt: 29.10.2011
	Halusin kovasti OSX käyttöjärjestelmän, ja asensin näihin aikoihin hackintosh käyttöjärjestelmän.
	Olin tehnyt sen aikaisemminkin.
	Tein sen vielä seuraavina vuosina pari kertaa, ja lopetin.
years.text:
This year, I moved back to my hometown and rediscovered my passion for programming.
I started programming again with the Perl programming language.

Why did I choose Perl over Python or other options? I'm not sure. A friend from university recommended Python to me, but I was certain that I didn't want to use it.
Perl somehow connected me to using Ubuntu as my desktop environment and also to my previous experience with Visual Basic. I had seen various programming language options in Linux for years.

Jayno.pl: 9/29/2011
	This is one of the first programs I wrote in a Linux environment.
	It uses a GTK2 window and a user interface designed with Glade.
	It takes a user inputted search term and searches it on Google.
	When Google returns a result, the URL is written in the GUI.
	I don't remember if this program ever worked properly.
	Now when I look at the code and understand Perl (even though I haven't used it since), I can see a few questionable sections.

pallotaustakuva.pl: 10/5/2011
	This program is essentially a shell script, but written in Perl.
	It retrieves an image from "fourmilab.ch/cgi-bin/Earth" and uses it as a desktop background for Finland.

graphviz.pl: 10/6/2011
	This program creates a graph with text inside circles, and the circles are connected by twisting lines and arrows.
	The circles, or nodes, represent places I have lived.
	The connections between the nodes show how I moved from one place to another.

asennus.txt: 10/29/2011
	I really wanted to have an OSX operating system, so I installed a hackintosh at this time.
	I had done it before.
	I even did it a couple more times in the following years before eventually stopping.

years.native_text:
Koko vuoden 2012 käytin kehitysympäristönä CodeBlocks:ia ja Linuxia tai FreeBSD:tä.

CPP Playground: kesä 2012
	Aloitin C++ ohjelmoimisen kesällä 2012.
	Tämä on ensimmäinen aito 'Hello World' projektini CodeBlocksilla.
	Siinä on "Hello World" cout:ia käyttämällä ja "funktio(4)", joka printtaa luvun 4 ja iteroi 10000 kertaa printaten numeron.

plot testi: kesä 2012
	Siinä käytetään mathgl2 kirjastoa "sin(pi*x)" käyrän piirtämiseen ja se kirjoitetaan png-kuvatiedostoksi.

KameraLataaja: kesä 2012
	Tämä on std c++ konsoliohjelma, joka kopioi kuvat Samsung Galaxy S (i9000) puhelimestani, ja tarvittaessa poistaa ne.
	Se on aika siisti kokonaisuus, ja siinä on ohjeet sen käyttämiseen.
	Tämä ohjelma käyttää std c++ kirjastoja ja boost kirjastoja.

PythonEmbd: kesä 2012
	Tässä on HelloWorld niminen luokka, joka perii Gtk::Window:in, joten tämä on ensimmäinen GUI ohjelmani c++:lla.
	En löydä ohjelmasta mitään Pythoniin viittaavaa, mutta luultavasti idea oli yhdistää c++, python ja gtk, jotta voisin ohjata sillä MetaTrader 4:sta, minkä tein tämän jälkeen.

Visu1: kesä 2012
	Forkkasin jonkun esimerkin "visualization library" kirjastolle (osoite visualizationlibrary.org).
	En saanut tätä esimerkkiä edes kääntymään.

3D Harjoittelua: kesä 2012
	Aloitin C++ ohjelmoimisen kesällä 2012.
	Ohjelma yrittää tehdä Ogre:lla yksinkertaisen 3D skenen, jossa on valo ja CloudyNoonSkyBox.

3D Harjoittelua 2: kesä 2012
	Tämäkin yrittää tehdä Ogre:lla yksinkertaisen 3D skenen, jossa on valo ja CloudyNoonSkyBox.

Forex++, F++, Fpp: 7.8.2012
	Tämä on ohjelma, joka yhdistää MetaTrader 4:seen skriptin, DLL:n, ja tcp yhteyden kautta.
	Siinä on mm. itsekirjoittamiani: FATL SATL signaalifiltterit, Bollinger Bands Squeeze, Mama, JMA, cycle periods, jne.
	Tämä oli toimiva ohjelma teknisesti, mutta ei se voittanut treidauksessa mitään.
	Kuitenkin, se jätti minuun suuren nälän tehdä forex-koodia, mikä johtui köyhyydestäni.
	Toisaalta, köyhyyteni takia minun olisi ollut järkevämpää tehdä musiikkia, mutta ympärilläni oli pelkästään toksisia ja haitallisia ihmisiä, jotka eivät tukeneet minua oikeaan suuntaan menemisessä.
	Ohjelmassa on Gtk gui, joka on suunniteltu Glade:lla.
	Kehitysympäristönä toimi CodeBlocks.
	Aluksi yhteyden hoiti zmq kirjasto, mutta yksi virstanpylväs oli käyttää suoraa tcp yhteyttä.

	Näin kirjoitin itse ohjelman otsakkeeseen:
		MetaTraderin GNU-pohjainen sijoitusautomaatio
	 	- Seppo Pakonen
		
		 1. Asenna ja suorita Forex++.mq4 skripti MetaTrader4:ssa (määritä myös oikea kansio PriceKeeper.cpp tiedostoon).
	 	2. Kirjoita Data/symbols tiedostoon halutut käytössä olevat valuuttaparit
	 	3. Laske mesa-indikaattorit valmiiksi suorittamalla ohjelma --mesainit parametrillä.
	 	4. Laske backtest eli harjoitusdata valmiiksi --backtest parametrillä.
	 	5. Laske suotuisat indikaattori-yhdistelmät (ns. koodisarjat) --btanalyzer parametrillä.
	 	6. Tee riskianalyysit indikaattori-yhdistelmille --btanalyzer2 parametrillä.
		    Laske suhteellinen osallistuminen indikaattori-yhdistelmille (stop loss ja take profit rajat)
years.text:
Throughout the year of 2012, I used CodeBlocks and Linux or FreeBSD as my development environment.

CPP Playground: summer 2012
	I started learning C++ in the summer of 2012.
	This is my first real 'Hello World' project using CodeBlocks.
	It includes a "Hello World" cout statement and a function(4) that prints the number 4 and iterates it 10,000 times.

plot test: summer 2012
	This project utilizes the mathgl2 library to plot a "sin(pi*x)" curve and then output it as a png image file.

CameraLoader: summer 2012
	This console application in std c++ copies images from my Samsung Galaxy S (i9000) phone and can also delete them if needed.
	It's a pretty neat package and includes instructions on how to use it.
	This program uses std c++ libraries as well as boost libraries.

PythonEmbd: summer 2012
	This project includes a HelloWorld class that inherits from Gtk::Window, making it my first GUI program in c++.
	I don't see anything related to Python in the code, but the idea was probably to combine c++, python, and gtk so that I could control MetaTrader 4, which I did afterwards.

Visu1: summer 2012
	I forked an example from the "visualization library" at visualizationlibrary.org.
	I couldn't even get this example to compile successfully.

3D Practice: summer 2012
	I started learning C++ in the summer of 2012.
	This program attempts to create a simple 3D scene using Ogre, with lighting and a CloudyNoonSkyBox.

3D Practice 2: summer 2012
	This project also attempts to create a simple 3D scene using Ogre, with lighting and a CloudyNoonSkyBox.

Forex++, F++, Fpp: August 7, 2012
	This is a program that combines a script, DLL, and a tcp connection to MetaTrader 4.
	It includes my own custom: FATL SATL signal filters, Bollinger Bands Squeeze, Mama, JMA, cycle periods, and more.
	Technically, this was a functional program, but it did not produce successful trades.
	However, it left me with a strong desire to continue writing forex code, which was largely driven by my poverty.
	On the other hand, due to my poverty, it would have been more sensible to focus on making music, but I was surrounded by toxic and harmful people who did not support me in moving in the right direction.
	The project includes a Gtk GUI designed with Glade.
	CodeBlocks was used as the development environment.
	Initially, the zmq library handled the connection, but I eventually switched to using a direct tcp connection.

This is how I wrote the header of the program:
	GNU-based Investment Automation for MetaTrader
	- Seppo Pakonen
	1. Install and run the Forex++.mq4 script in MetaTrader 4 (also specify the correct directory in the PriceKeeper.cpp file).
	2. Write the desired currency pairs to the Data/symbols file.
	3. Prepare the indicator calculations by running the program with the --mesainit parameter.
	4. Prepare the backtest data using the --backtest parameter.
	5. Calculate favorable indicator combinations (known as code series) using the --btanalyzer parameter.
	6. Perform risk analyses for the indicator combinations using the --btanalyzer2 parameter.
		Calculate relative participation for the indicator combinations (stop loss and take profit boundaries).
